## Introduction
Boss bars can dynamically update their progress and title for timers or event tracking.

### Example: Countdown Boss Bar
```java
Bukkit.getScheduler().runTaskTimer(plugin, new BukkitRunnable() {
    double progress = 1.0;
    @Override
    public void run() {
        progress -= 0.05;
        if(progress <= 0) {
            bar.removePlayer(player);
            cancel();
        } else {
            bar.setProgress(progress);
            bar.setTitle("§cTime remaining: " + (int)(progress*20) + "s");
        }
    }
}, 0L, 20L); // Every second
```

### Logic Explanation
- `setProgress()` updates the fill dynamically.
- `setTitle()` updates the displayed message.
- Scheduled tasks allow countdowns or live updates.

### Edge Cases & Warnings
- Avoid updating every tick unnecessarily; use a reasonable interval.
- Always remove players to prevent invisible bars lingering.
- Rapid updates may cause client visual glitches.
